level 0
keywords enchant
---
Syntax: enchant show
        enchant buy <enchantment>

Permanently enchants a wearable item using a spell matrix and enchantment
objects from your inventory. This system allows players to customize
equipment with stat bonuses at a quest-point cost.

Setup required before enchanting:
  1. Obtain a spell matrix object (ITEM_SPELL_MATRIX) and hold it.
  2. Place one wearable item (weapon, armor, or light) in your inventory.
  3. Place one or more enchantment objects (ITEM_ENCHANTMENT) in the matrix.

  enchant show    -- Preview what the enchantment would do: displays current
                     stats, proposed stats, total costs, and whether the
                     combination is legal.
  enchant buy     -- Commits the enchantment, deducts quest points from your
                     total, consumes the enchantment items, and permanently
                     modifies the target item.

Stat limits and rules:
  - Ability stats (STR/INT/DEX/WIS/CON): Combined total must not exceed +1.
  - Maximum HP/mana bonus: 480. Maximum move bonus: 240.
  - Maximum hitroll/damroll: 50 each.
  - Minimum armor class: -480. Minimum saves: -36.
  - Base cost: 20 quest points.  Unique items cost 20 QP less.
  - You must be at least the item's level to enchant it.

Restrictions:
  - Clan equipment cannot be enchanted.
  - All transactions are logged via the brands system.

See also: qpspend worth appraise
